The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 1.9 percent to 24,051.62. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  climbed 2 percent to 3,031.06.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the worldâ€™s fourth-largest tin
producer, rose 4.1 percent to 3.30 soles after futures surged in
 London .  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner,
climbed 3.2 percent to $4.48 after gold advanced in  New York ,
said Angel Alcala, a trader at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados
SAB.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, gained 3.7 percent to 56 centimos after sugar rose as
much as 0.5 percent in New York.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, gained for a third day,
jumping 3.8 percent to $1.36 after the company announced it
started operations at its ethanol project.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, rose 2.8 percent to 1.09 soles after
crude rallied in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
